# Instance-owned files: framework tag-merges never overwrite these.
# Git uses the "ours" merge strategy for any merge (including `git merge <tag>`),
# keeping the instance's version and discarding the incoming framework change.
#
# REQUIRED once per clone (not version-controlled, so it cannot ship here):
#   git config merge.ours.driver true
# The `ours` driver is not built into git; without that config line every
# `merge=ours` below silently no-ops. `/upgrade` and docs/runbook/UPGRADE.md set
# it. Adopters: add your own instance-specific files below.

CLAUDE.md merge=ours
README.md merge=ours
place.config.ts merge=ours
knowledge/** merge=ours
public/media/** merge=ours
CNAME merge=ours
docs/baselines/** merge=ours
scripts/ci/genericity-denylist.local.txt merge=ours
